Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @green beans{80}, then cut into thirds. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10}, @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs with half the garlic.

Add the @British pork mince{240%g} to the breadcrumb bowl, season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Shape into mini sausage shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas, then pop onto a #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Couscous ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large saucepan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pour in the @water{240%ml} for the couscous, stir in the @chicken stock paste{1%tsp} and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{120%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan and leave to the side for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

== Fresh Tomato & Red Wine Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the tomatoes and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until they start to soften and break down, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @ground cumin{1%tsp}, @dried oregano{1%tsp} and remaining garlic to the pan. Fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @red wine stock paste{28%g} and @water{150%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once thickened, taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} if needed.

Remove from the heat, adding a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== To Serve ==

Once the koftas are cooked, stir them gently through the tomato sauce so they're well coated.

Fluff up the couscous and beans with a #fork{}, then spoon into your #bowls{}.

Top with the soutzoukakia style koftas, spooning over all the tomato sauce from the pan.

Enjoy!